Module 1: Inputs
Ideally, any city could input their databases, even if they don't use the same features, classifications, and weights

property_data.csv
Database of all taxable city properties with features that impact value + location

businesses.csv
Database of businesses with "id" column to match the business with its corresponding property

made_payment.csv
Database of properties that made a payment in 2024

For property_type, structure_type, property_features:
Restructure the data to create dummy variables (or one-hot-encoding).

Example: The variable "window_material" has values: "Wood", "No Windows", "Breeze Block", "Sliding panels with aluminium frame", "Traditional glazed casement set in metal frame or wood frame", "Louvre". This should be updated to: "window_material_wood", "window_material_no_windows", "window_material_breeze_block", "window_material_sliding_panels_with_aluminium_frame", "window_material_traditional_glazed_casement_set_in_metal_frame_or_wood_frame", and "window_material_louvre", each with values "yes" and "no"
